<div id="review_2938474374" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2938474374" />
    <a title="Asaria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44427430-asaria"><img alt="Asaria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609958434p2/44427430.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2938474374?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Asaria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Asaria" href="/user/show/44427430-asaria">Asaria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8438008-the-heptameron">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44427430-asaria?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44427430-asaria?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44427430-asaria?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44427430-asaria?shelf=literature-french-francophone">literature-french-francophone</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44427430-asaria?shelf=16th-century-literature">16th-century-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2938474374" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6487139492988841753">War of sexes or French response to Boccaccio&apos;s The Decameron? There, where Decameron is exuberant and praising the exploration of human sexuality and having fun in general, Heptameron positions itself in the opposition. Praise the honor of the participants! <br/><br/>As a married woman, you mustn&apos;t seek out love outside of marital bed. Chastity, nobility and bad endings, that&apos;s your virtues. Although the book is a product of its time, I think even a modern reader might find these short stories enjoyable. </span>
  <span id="freeText6487139492988841753" style="display:none">War of sexes or French response to Boccaccio's The Decameron? There, where Decameron is exuberant and praising the exploration of human sexuality and having fun in general, Heptameron positions itself in the opposition. Praise the honor of the participants! <br /><br />As a married woman, you mustn't seek out love outside of marital bed. Chastity, nobility and bad endings, that's your virtues. Although the book is a product of its time, I think even a modern reader might find these short stories enjoyable. For sure I did. Smart women, depraved monks, (un)faithful lovers. However, a more sensitive person might be triggered by the way rape is presented or inequality of French society back then. Another drawback is in longer-term the plots become repetitive.<br /><br />Luckily for us, the storytellers don't hold back and comment on the things they don't like. That very often leads to heated discussions with women or men defending their opinions or pulling a common front against what they consider wrong. I kept waiting for these arguments in the interludes. They show XVI century morality.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6487139492988841753" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

