      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/281380.Marguerite_de_Navarre">About Marguerite de Navarre</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/281380.Marguerite_de_Navarre"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1211921634p3/281380.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/281380.Marguerite_de_Navarre">Marguerite de Navarre
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
26
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer7612765497550237357">Marguerite de Navarre, also known as Marguerite d&apos;Angoulême and Margaret of Navarre, was the queen consort of King Henry II of Navarre. As patron of humanists and reformers, and as an author in her own right, she was an outstanding figure of the French Renaissance. Samuel Putnam called her &quot;The First Modern Woman&quot;.</span>
  <span id="freeText7612765497550237357" style="display:none">Marguerite de Navarre, also known as Marguerite d'Angoulême and Margaret of Navarre, was the queen consort of King Henry II of Navarre. As patron of humanists and reformers, and as an author in her own right, she was an outstanding figure of the French Renaissance. Samuel Putnam called her "The First Modern Woman".</span>
  <a data-text-id="7612765497550237357" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

